title: Grateful Dead Live at Hartford Civic Center on 1977-05-28
lineage: Bettyboard 7 inch master reel @ 7.5 ips > DAT(zero gen) > Sony PCM R-700 > HHb CDR-800 > CDR > CDR (first gen) > EAC > SHN
description: Bertha-> Good Lovin'-> Sugaree, Jack Straw, Row Jimmy, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Passenger, Brown Eyed Women, Promised Land Samson & Delilah, Tennessee Jed, Estimated Prophet-> Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Playin' In The Band-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Excellent This show is right in sync with all of May 77.  Sound quality is pretty good, and the beats are outstanding.

Best Show EVER Without a doubt, the best and most underrated show in existence.  The SOUND IS AWESOME, and again, the best Sugaree EVER!  See for your self.
INCREDIBLE.  I have a few hundred shows, this is still my favorite.

Sugaree Thanks for the tip, fremontbob.

That is one for the books.  Jerry explores every inch of the space without once stepping out of the box.  The lazy blues pace of the last movement is particularly fine.

I'm also keen on the Row Jimmy which trudges across the tundra like an Imperial Walker on its way back to the moisture farm for another injection of Dantooine yam-yam.
help hey im new to this, and i am having trouble getting the stream recordings of all the songs, i can only manage to get the first song onto my itunes! doesnt anyone have any tips! Thanks
First Dead Show This was the first show I went to and became a true dead head from that day on.  saw over 100 shows since then.

oh yeah! 77' I believe 77 is the FINEST vintage Dead . . .Without Pigpen,that is. May of 77 may be the highest peak the boys ever reached . . even Donna is on the ball.  They were really cookin' that night.  And on my effin birthday? . . .What a rad site this is!

If I Had My Way I was sitting pretty high up at this one, and Tennessee Jed had such a powerful upward surge that the phrase 'blow the roof off' seemed apt.  A few weeks later, the Civic Center had to close for a while, due to structural damage to the roof!

Shake It, Shake It Beautiful Show
